e- and post-Soviet poets Andrei Sen-Sen'kov, Arkadii Dragomoshchenko, and Kirill Medvede, to understand their fascination with the visual language, representational power, and metaphorical possibilities offered by the camera and the photographic image. Within the context of long-standing anxieties about the threat that visual media pose to literary culture, Blasing finds that these poets were attracted to the affinities and tensions that exist between the lyric or elegy and the snapshot. Snapshots of the Soul reveals that at the core of each poet's approach to "writing the photograph" is the urge to demonstrate the superior ability of poetic language to capture and convey human experience  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLiterature and photographyzRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLiterature and photographyzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aPhotography in literature. 0aRussian poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aPhotography. 4aPoetry & Criticism. 4aSoviet & East European History. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh  aPoetry and photography, 20th Century Russian poetry, Marina Tsvetaeva, BorisPasternak, Joseph Brodsky, Bella Akhmadulina.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU0 cprintz978150175369540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978